column7: most to find employment. None are turned away
column8: and the slums outside the cathedrals swell with thousands of willing servants to the Bodhisattva most high."

There we make our own classes and rules as we expericen the play. use it if you like it :) its free and basicly me and one more makes the changes there :) Anyway thanks for this amazing initiative. I realy love the job and effort you are putting in to this."

"4. Describe Your Location": "The ruins of a great fortress city
column2: corrupted by dark magic and greed which led to its eventual collapse in ruin. Great statues once guarded its gates
column3: steps of carved stone leading to a large fortress capped with menacing spires like speartips prodding the sky. Now its all cracked and crumbling
column4: statues misshapen by neglect (or residual dark magic)
column5: some having their faces mysteriously broken away into fragmented skulls. The fortress hugs the mountainside
column6: which is cragged and steep. A snowmelt stream tumbles down from the peak above
column7: cutting through the fortress on one side before exiting in a waterfall at the edge of the fortress side (the stairs from the gate are beside the falls
column8: making the stones treacherously slick and the drop from them steep). Few evergreen trees occupy this altitude
column9: and the ones near the fortress are dead and haunting
column10: looking as if they could snare passers-by with their barren limbs. It's a perfect home for death
column11: and it willingly grants it to any unscrupulous visitor."

"8. Describe Your Terrain
column2: Border Terrain And Biome.": "The terrain is mountainous
column3: part of a massive range of jagged peaks like teeth of some leviathan's maw. Snow constantly caps many of the peaks
column4: creating many small rivers and waterfalls throughout
column5: all flowing down into a larger body nearby (lake
column6: ocean
column8: depending on nearby location). Lush forests
column10: grow at its base. Trails cut through the forest disappear quickly
column11: the woods quick to reclaim what's theirs once again
column12: making it very easy for the average traveler to get lost. The fortress was built for the gold and jewels harvested from mountain stone
column13: though the rock here is very tough and unforgiving. In addition to the rough stone and thick forest growth
column14: the lower terrain also host numerous formidable creatures
column15: from large spiders to ferocious greystone panthers and everything inbetween."

column1: "9.B. Using The Key Ideas Of The Styles Given
column2: You Can Add Some Flourish?": "The fortress was constructed of harshly cut stone
column4: but constructed by men. Statues are usually imposing
column5: like armored knights with shield and sword
column6: or fearsome creatures. The front gate to the steps is guarded by twin knights with massive shields
column7: intricately detailed and at the ready
column8: as if they could spring to life and battle at any moment. The steps rise up beside the waterfall
column9: with occasional outcroppings for statues or guardposts where the terrain allowed. The black magic conducted at the castle appears to have had an affect over all of it
column10: turning even the stone darker. The once sturdy construction now crumbles
column11: falling away sometimes with the faintest touch while other cracks hold firm. Skeletons of the dead can be found throughout the territory
column12: grim reminders of how lethal the area can be."

column1: "10. What Text Do You Want To Appear In The Document For This Location? (2 Paragraph Maximum)": "Vonnarath's Keep
column2: now known more as Vonnarath's Crypt
column4: built from heavy stone mined from the mountain. Its wealth grew rapidly
column5: fed with gold and jewels pulled from deep in the mountain. But greed corrupts
column6: and the heart of Vonnarath grew darker with every jewel extracted from the stone. It is believe some of those very treasures harbored an evil in their faceted glimmers
column7: and before long the master of Vonnarath himself delved into the dark magical arts. The reach of evil spread beyond the fortress walls
column8: spreading to the forests like a plague
column9: inviting the foulest of creatures to surface. Vonnarath fell to its own evils
column10: the darkness consuming every soul until no man remained alive. Now it sits in deathly silence
column12: its halls dark. But it is not abandoned. Something still dwells there
column13: though what evil it is remains a mystery. It’s rumored that a massive treasure still sits deep within Vonnarath’s belly
column14: guarded by a fearsome creature beyond all evils. Some say it’s a great black dragon
column15: a serpent of fire and ash. Others tell of a massive spider
column17: fangs glistening with hunger beneath eight eyes of pure blackness. Still others say it’s a demon pulled from the seven hells through the dark magic
column18: a hulking creature of living stone veined with magma and a lust for destruction. No one knows for sure
column19: for no soul has visited Vonnarath and lived to tell."

column10: as if the evils had not yet reached out from the deep forest to its edges

column1: "10. What Text Do You Want To Appear In The Document For This Location? (2 Paragraph Maximum)": "Gilborn
column3: and his trusty Canine companion Rose
column4: went on hundreds of adventures together seeking out magic artifacts and shiny new treasures. Something
column5: happened on one such adventure
column6: that made Rose dissappear. Gilborn would not talk about it
column7: never discussing what happened to her. Gilborn traveled to the largest and closest rock formation he could
column8: and began to carve his trusty companion into the cliffside. He wanted it to be seen from afar so she would run back to him
column9: as in her satchel were many valuable maps and treasures. Dwarves from all over the many plains came to Gilborns aid to construct this gigantic monument. Years
column11: it took to construct this monument. But alas
column12: she never came. From all around the surrounding areas this gigantic dog could be seen. Gilborn had set up camp
column13: and over the time of construction
column14: he inspired others to do the same
column15: forming a small community. Some traders set up a small town to capitalise on the artistry at hand
column16: to share tales and rumours to new travelers
column17: to seek out Rose's treasure. Once the monument had been fully erected
column22: except from a few roses growing at the base of the statue. Later
column24: other wild and undomesticted animals gathered to the statue
column25: something magical drawing them maybe. Adventurers that gathered would tame these animals and have a companion of their own
column26: and some even setting out to find Rose and collect Gilborn treasure."
